name: Bridge over 42nd street
description: The one advantage to winter is that sunset is now a much more manageable part of the day to be energized to go and shoot cityscapes. The only issue is the cold. I was also trying to get more into City images. Shooting in the parks was fun but it is so close to landscapes that it felt like I needed to push myself out of my comfort zone a bit and try doing more of something I am not so practiced at. This is an iconic street in midtown. I am looking from a bridge on the east side of Manhattan looking all the way down 42nd Street. I hope you enjoy the view as much as I did waiting for the light to be just right!
